The gui.py script establishes a graphical user interface (GUI) using PyQt5, featuring a main window (MainGUI) and two sidebars (LeftSidebar and RightSidebar).
The setup includes basic configuration like window title, size, and the addition of sidebars, but there's no direct integration with speech recognition or command execution functionality so good.
Hier sind deine Ziele:
Enhance Speech Recognition:
Ensure the script can continuously listen to audio input and output recognized text.
Handle exceptions and errors gracefully.
Ersetze alle Platzhalter in den Skripten mit ausführbarem, Code. schreibe den code ausführlich. 

Modify GUI Script:
Add a text display area or notification system to show recognized speech.
Provide visual feedback for voice command recognition and processing.
Add controls for starting/stopping the speech recognition process.
Ersetze alle Platzhalter in den Skripten mit ausführbarem, Code. schreibe den code ausführlich. 

Integrate Speech Recognition with GUI:
Connect the speech recognition output to the GUI display.
Enable the GUI to control the speech recognition (start/stop listening).
Ersetze alle Platzhalter in den Skripten mit ausführbarem, Code. schreibe den code ausführlich. 

Integrate Command Execution:
Link recognized speech to the command execution script.
Provide feedback in the GUI for successful or failed command execution.
Ersetze alle Platzhalter in den Skripten mit ausführbarem, Code. schreibe den code ausführlich. 

Testing and Debugging:
Thoroughly test the integrated system.
Debug and optimize performance.
Documentation and Comments:
Add detailed comments and documentation for each part of the code.
To integrate with the speech recognition system, consider the following enhancements:
Display Recognized Speech: Add a text display area or notification system in the GUI to show recognized speech.
Voice Command Feedback: Provide visual feedback in the GUI when a voice command is recognized and processed.
GUI Interaction with Speech Recognition: Enable the GUI to control or interact with the speech recognition system, such as starting or stopping listening.
